	     <tr><td valign="top" id="fs8" class="mform"><span id="notbold">By:</span> <a href="/db/poster.html?user=310868"><span id="Scholar">Kalaylus</span></a><br /><b><span id="Scholar">Scholar</span></b><br /><span id="notbold">93 posts<br /><span id="notbold">Score</span>: Decent [3.06]</td><td valign=top class="mform" width="100%"><p>The effect on the robe is cast on yourself, not on the mob.&nbsp;&nbsp;It is a short-term focus buff that lowers the resist rate of YOUR spells by 40%.  So a smart chanter would probably do tash (virtually unresistable) then click the robe then drop a slow, cripple, asphyxiate if we're talking a single mob encounter.  If he is mezzing, he would be best off clicking the robe first then throwing mezzes on all the mobs he could before the effect runs out, then tashing and establishing control.  In a group situation would most likely be used for things like an add coming with the named, well you click the robe and that add is mezzed and the named is slowed with less resists.<br/><br/>Quite useful, a lot more so than some of the effects on the other OoW BPs.</p>&nbsp;<br /></td></tr>
